title: Labor Cost Per Dollar of Real Gross National Product for United States
notes:
The Compensation Of Employees (National Income Component) Is Expressed In Percentage Of Gross National Product In 1958 Dollars. Data Are At Annual Rates. Source: Survey Of Current Business, Supplement, August 1966, "The National Income And Product Accounts Of The United States, 1929-1965."

This NBER data series q08300 appears on the NBER website in Chapter 8 at http://www.nber.org/databases/macrohistory/contents/chapter08.html.
